00:47:34.888 --> 00:47:36.818
overturning circulation.

00:47:36.818 --> 00:47:43.115
During this hiatus only since about the
year 2000 a new pattern of winds developed

00:47:43.115 --> 00:47:50.467
over the Arctic Ocean. It's called the
Arctic Dipole Anomaly. This pair of winds

00:47:50.467 --> 00:47:57.902
going in opposite direction drives ice and
sea and fresh water from the Arctic into

00:47:57.902 --> 00:48:04.361
the north Atlantic where it will shut off
or it can impede. Where it collides,

00:48:04.361 --> 00:48:09.418
basically, with the Gulf Stream and at
that collision point the water sinks to

00:48:09.418 --> 00:48:11.368
depth and we did see that.

00:48:11.368 --> 00:48:18.498
This is a small event of something that
actually happened in the historical record

00:48:18.498 --> 00:48:26.480
8,000 years ago as the ice sheet was
retreating across North America. As it

00:48:26.480 --> 00:48:32.411
retreated, it left behind in the area of
Hudson Bay a huge glacial lake that was

00:48:32.411 --> 00:48:37.611
contained between the melting ice on one
hand and the moraine that pushed up on the

00:48:37.611 --> 00:48:43.135
front. These glacial moraines are unstable
and there was a huge outflow of water that

00:48:43.135 --> 00:48:48.862
occurred all at once and there was a 200
year period of cool climate that then

00:48:48.862 --> 00:48:50.203
recovered.

00:48:50.203 --> 00:48:55.728
The Columbia River was also formed this
way. What the satellites have observed is

00:48:55.728 --> 00:49:02.166
a great injection of fresh water into this
Gyre here the Beaufort Gyre that began at

00:49:02.166 --> 00:49:08.625
approximately the same time and that water
is lighter. When it gets to the saltier

00:49:08.625 --> 00:49:11.775
Atlantic the saltier Atlantic will sink.

00:49:11.775 --> 00:49:17.462
So here is the next and most important
point. This sea ice retreat that I just

00:49:17.462 --> 00:49:24.144
documented is warming the Arctic by a very
simple mechanism. When you replace white

00:49:24.144 --> 00:49:31.924
ice with blue ocean you absorb much more
solar energy. Sea ice itself may reflect

00:49:31.924 --> 00:49:39.866
half back to space and the ocean absorbs
93% of the energy that's falling on it. As

00:49:39.866 --> 00:49:44.336
the sea ice retreats, it warms the Arctic.

00:49:44.336 --> 00:49:51.465
A recent paper that came out from Scripps
measured the degree of warming since the

00:49:51.465 --> 00:49:58.615
satellite era started in '79 and they
found that the net sea ice retreat adds

00:49:58.615 --> 00:50:03.600
about six watts per meter
squared, but two thirds of the heating

00:50:03.600 --> 00:50:10.450
that took place in that period occurred in
those 10 years between '01 and '11. The

00:50:10.450 --> 00:50:15.830
Arctic is small but if you average this
over the globe you get 0.21 watts per

00:50:15.830 --> 00:50:21.570
meter squared which is about a quarter of
the increase that you would have expected

00:50:21.570 --> 00:50:24.800
from the increase in greenhouse gas at
that time.

00:50:24.800 --> 00:50:30.650
So you have added a new warning mechanism
that the climate, at least in recent

00:50:30.650 --> 00:50:38.830
times, was not used to. This is a picture
of the geography of heat transport in the

00:50:38.830 --> 00:50:44.810
climate and I put it on even though it's
complicated just to remind you that the

00:50:44.810 --> 00:50:50.460
basic circulation of the atmosphere as
understood from the time of Edmond Halley

00:50:50.460 --> 00:50:57.050
was there was heavy and strong warming of
the ocean and land over the tropics. This

00:50:57.050 --> 00:51:03.810
heat was then transported to the north. So
it's a north south circulation-- north

00:51:03.810 --> 00:51:08.760
equator to pole circulation that is the
fundamental feature of our climate

00:51:08.760 --> 00:51:09.860
transport.

00:51:09.860 --> 00:51:17.450
If you suddenly add a new heating source
at the poles particularly the Arctic won't

00:51:17.450 --> 00:51:23.740
you change the circulation of heat in the
atmosphere? And will this not, in fact,

00:51:23.740 --> 00:51:32.540
lead to states like the El Nino? What we
do know and this a question still under

00:51:32.540 --> 00:51:41.120
active investigation, but what we do know
is that we have created a 17 or 18 year

00:51:41.120 --> 00:51:47.040
persistent La Niña-like state in the
Pacific Ocean and also a similar outflow

00:51:47.040 --> 00:51:54.280
in the north Atlantic that is lasting
longer than most typical La Niña's lasted

00:51:54.280 --> 00:51:56.140
the whole period of time.

00:51:56.140 --> 00:52:01.110
What this has had an effect on the climate
down below because when you're in a La

00:52:01.110 --> 00:52:09.220
Niña state, you bend the jet stream as you
see and you've seen many many pictures

00:52:09.220 --> 00:52:13.890
recently anytime you look at the weather
you'll see the jet stream dipping deep

00:52:13.890 --> 00:52:24.100
into central United States. We've remained
in a state of La Niña-like jet stream. The

00:52:24.100 --> 00:52:26.790
weather patterns, then, correlate with
this.

00:52:26.790 --> 00:52:33.780
Now the question is the global
temperatures have been constant so you

00:52:33.780 --> 00:52:40.540
would expect that there would be many
fewer heat waves or at least the same

00:52:40.540 --> 00:52:47.740
number as before. This has not proven the
