00:52:55.360 --> 00:53:02.430
Europe for the last 500 years since 1500.
What you see is five of the ten years in

00:53:02.430 --> 00:53:08.891
the 2010 decade were the hottest years on
record.

00:53:08.891 --> 00:53:16.264
You also hear about this unstable. You
hear this bending La Niña-like jet stream.

00:53:16.264 --> 00:53:23.231
You hear about it in another context
because in the winter it brings Arctic air

00:53:23.231 --> 00:53:28.309
to the south and it's then responsible for
the large snow storms that we've seen in

00:53:28.309 --> 00:53:35.857
the past. We also know that the La Niña
state implies a very dry climate in

00:53:35.857 --> 00:53:39.920
California, something that we are
presently observing.

